writing 3'b111 will mask the Nerror propagation to pad Writing 3'b000 will unmask the Nerror propagation to pad

writing '111' enables a single cycle wait state with respect to CR5A_clk for rom access. This needs to be set when R5 clock is at 400MHZ and Interconnect-clk is at 200MHZ. (because it is a timing issue in this scenario)
writing 3'b111 will trigger the reset FSM. Reset FSM ensures reset to R5SS and inturn ensures the latching of lock_step and also mem_swap bit
writing 3'b111 ensures switch happens only after R5SS reset. Orelse it will be a immediate switch.

writing 3'b000 ensures R5 to be in Dual-Core mode. Note: The change happens after the R5SS reset assertion if R5_CONTROL_lock_step_switch_wait is set. Or else the switiching to Dual-core happens on the fly.
writing 3'b111 ensures ROM-Eclipsing happens only after R5SS reset. Orelse it will be a immediate change.
writing '111' ensures eclipsing of CR5A_ROM immediately if memswap_wait is not set. If memswap_wait is set then ROM is eclipsed after R5SS reset assertion.
writing '000' will unhalt CR5A. This register should be written only once.
writing '000' will unhalt for CR5B. This register should be written only once.
Reading 1: confirms R5SS is in lockstep mode. Reading 0: confirms R5SS is in Dual-core mode.
